message.content:
1. Simple Past Tense: This is used to talk about past actions that happened once and are complete. For example, "I went to school yesterday."

2. Present Perfect Tense: This is used to talk about an action that started in the past and continues up to the present moment. For example, "I have lived in New York for two years."

3. Past Continuous Tense: This is used to describe an action that was happening when something else happened in the past. For example, "I was watching television while my friend called me."

4. Present Continuous Tense: This is used to talk about actions or states that are continuing up to the present moment. For example, "I am studying right now."

5. Future Simple Tense: This is used to talk about future actions that will happen only once. For example, "I will go to the store tomorrow."

6. Future Continuous Tense: This is used to talk about an action that will be happening when something else happens in the future. For example, "By next year, I will have finished my degree."
